The writer of today's letter was originally from Suining, Sichuan Province. On January 31, after the outbreak of the COVID-19 epidemic, he received a request from his work unit and began a 1,780-kilometer journey back to Beijing. Along the way, he recorded his experiences with photos and text.

My 3,000-mile drive back to Beijing

By the North Red Seven

January 31 at noon, the unit notice requirements, leave Beijing to the rest of the staff, in addition to Hubei Province, the same day back to Beijing, Beijing after self-isolation 14 days. I decided to drive 1,780 km back to Beijing from my hometown in Suining, Sichuan, on February 1.

Write down what you see, hear and think along the way here, as a remembrance of this special day, but also to prepare friends from the field back to Beijing road trip reference.

A trip to Sichuan and Shaanxi

I plan to drive from Sichuan to Beijing in two days, passing through Shaanxi, Shanxi and Hebei. Planning for the first day back in Beijing is relatively simple. From Suining, it starts to the northeast along the Suixi Expressway —————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— --.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Choose the first day back to Beijing route, ready to Xi'an near a night

At 9:40 on February 1, I drove from my hometown in Suining to Beijing. There was no inspection at the entrance to the motorway, and the journey was smooth, with little traffic, and 204 kilometres at a stretch to the lower BA temple service area in Bazhong.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
No entry without a mask, standard in high-speed service areas. There is a Typo in the picture

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
MYRICA Rubra, a gas pump attendant, was busy filling up and charging, and her co workers took turns eating lunch

There weren't many cars filled up, and it was noon, and only one gas man was running in and out. The oiler, named Myrica Rubra, has worked in Sichuan Jiaotong Zhongyou Energy Co. , Ltd. for five years, and has been working here for nine consecutive days since the Lunar New Year's twenty-nine. Her home is more than 60 kilometers away in Nanjiang County, and she was unable to reunite with her family for the Spring Festival. Many ordinary people who work in this way support the normal functioning of society.

At 5:30, I entered the Qin Mountains Service area. Vehicles are parked near the high-speed parking platform, passengers have to walk about 150 meters to enter the supermarket, or to the toilet. There are a lot of vehicles stopping here. The platform parking lot is estimated to hold more than 50 vehicles. This segregation of parking areas and service cores is also part of the epidemic.

In the service area, I'm going to book a hotel for the night. After reading the information on Wechat and the Internet, I realized that the high-speed entrance of Xi'an into the city had set up guard and quarantine inspection one after another. I didn't know how long it would take, so I decided not to go to Xi'an for lodging at all, and to drive a little further ahead, so that I could travel early the next morning. So I searched for a place to stay that night, and I ended up in Fuping County, Weinan, Xi Zhongxun's hometown.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Long queues of vehicles at Fuping County Expressway exit for quarantine inspection.

All the way clear, and all the way safe, everyone was driving carefully, along the road did not find an accident. 7:40 pm, out of Xiyu high-speed fuping exit, traffic jam, do not ask also know, is subject to quarantine inspection. Less than 300 meters of road section, front and back long lines, 5 to 8 minutes to move a few parking spaces.

We wait patiently. Half an hour, an hour... it doesn't look like much traffic. I don't know why it's so slow. On the Internet, Mount Hua reported on January 27 that a joint inspection team from the transportation, transportation, health, forestry and other departments was conducting a one-on-one inspection of passing vehicles at the fuping exit of Xiyu Expressway in Foshan. With so many departments involved, it's a big effort, but it won't be short. I figure if there's 30 cars in front of me at the checkpoint, I'll have to check them every five minutes, and it'll take me 150 minutes, which is two and a half hours.

Out of the first high-speed vehicles into three teams of four, near the exit found only two lanes of traffic, do not dare to squeeze the car into the old channel. I waited in line on the far left for an hour and a half, only to find that I had to share an aisle with the right side. Ahead of a car hesitantly did not dare to come forward, the right side of the car filed into. Two highway workers, wearing reflective suits, stand 50 meters ahead. I made it clear in the past that I was going to ask them to help smooth out the queue, and the two queues zipped together into one.

One of them said you were coordinating, asked me if I was cutting in line, said you were standing in three lanes instead of two. He also asked me to open the double flash, I followed the line, at the same time to the two teams of five cars at the same time hail, please cooperate with a little, zip to let the way. Several car owners are wearing masks, no one said anything, but all nodded in silence. Finally he got into the driveway and continued his snail-like movement.

When bored, listen to the radio to see if you can understand the local epidemic situation. Search for a long time, but only a recommendation "strong brain Xinkang" sell medicine program. "You only need to spend 1192 yuan, buy two courses, then send two courses of treatment... " this unreliable selling medicine broadcast, often heard along the way. If a local radio station at this time to provide local epidemic prevention information, especially to the high-speed export vehicle owners some practical information, not for the people?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Checkpoint staff were fully armed and taking temperature readings for passengers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Joint Quarantine Inspection Post, 5 staff to check and fill in the passenger information.

At the joint quarantine inspection station, the inspectors took the temperature of the passengers, asked if there was any live meat on board, and then asked me to take my driver's license and ID card to register where I had come from and where I was going. An elderly inspector heard me say he was going to Beijing. "How did it get to us? " He wondered. I said I'm from Suining. I'll stop here for one night. "The industry and Commerce Bureau asks the hotel not to open, where do you live? " I said that has already reserved the hotel, is in the fuping station street east section. He knew about the hotel, so he used. Maybe the registration time is too long. He can't see the ID card number clearly. Ask everyone to read it to him.

It took me two hours and 40 minutes from 17:42, when I got off the highway and started queuing, to pass inspection and drive into fuping at 22:21. This 300-meter wait feels like the longest distance in the world. Driving into fuping city, the streets are empty. On either side of the street is a long clay lamp decorated with the words "rich peace" , which is the implication of the name of the county.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The city is full of the words "affluence and peace" .

Through the shansi-hopei

In the hotel, consider the next day back to Beijing trip, want to choose a route may be less cars, far point is not afraid, if the encounter quarantine inspection, the waiting time may be shorter. Finally, we choose this route: The beijing-kunming Expressway, foshan-foshan-qingyin Expressway, the other two expressway, foshan-xinzhou Expressway, foshan-foshan Expressway, the whole route is 1068 km from Fuping County, after Linfen, Taiyuan, Xinzhou, Mount Wutai, and then Baoding Fuping County, Beijing Han Village River into Beijing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I ended up taking the longer route back to Beijing, which probably involved fewer cars.

February 2nd, 6:30, wheels up. It was dark and empty. A large sign for a hip-hop club above the hotel building was on. A light on the ground floor next to it indicated a yoga studio on the seventh floor. Hip-hop, Yoga, maybe a reflection of normal life in Fuping County. Back home in Suining, my mother's square dancing stopped long before the Spring Festival. Perhaps dancing is a sign of a peaceful world, recalled the German boy Qiao Qiao, who had watched the movie Jojo's fantasy on the Internet the other day, and asked the Jewish girl hiding in his house what would be the first thing she would do if the war stopped? "Dancing. ". As the American flag flies through the city streets, they stand in front of their homes and begin to dance..

On the high-speed, into the fuping service area to fill a tank of gas. The banner on the convenience store's display said, "salute to the medical workers who are fighting the epidemic in the front line. " The three women were on duty wearing masks. They were also dedicated to the logistics of fighting the epidemic. They were faced with people from all over the world every day, not Without risk of infection.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A reminder not to get out of the car.

Around 8:30, through the Longmen Yellow River Bridge, from Shaanxi into Shanxi. The Longmen Yellow River Bridge Toll Station was demolished on September 30,2019, in accordance with the country's requirements for the demolition of high-speed toll stations at provincial boundaries. The bridge is the capital-kunming expressway connecting Shanxi and Shaanxi provinces, there have been news reports that the average daily flow of more than 20,000 vehicles. But this Spring Festival, the traffic drops off.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Longmen Yellow River Bridge, which marks the shaanxi-shanxi border, was demolished ahead of the 2019 National Day holiday

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Taiyuan East Service area, after the staff on duty to prevent reminders, he returned to wear a mask after entering the toilet.

The male toilet in the service area is pasted with the bold words: "The road of civilization, only half a step" . The civilization of defecation should be constantly reminded that the toilet revolution is still a matter for the country's leaders to worry about. How many steps to ecological civilization?

This new coronavirus outbreak, but also the people of "eat civilization" torture. It has to do with overeating game. Some people can't keep their mouths shut. Birds like the yellow-breasted bunting, commonly known as the "Bluebird" , fly from Siberia, Russia, to southern China for the winter, but are killed in large numbers along the way, many fatalized and killed, and sent to venison tables in places like Guangdong. The yellow-breasted bunting was upgraded from "endangered" to "critically endangered" in a 2017 International Union for Conservation of Nature Update, and was "not endangered" until 2013. I have seen several yellow-breasted bunting in the Yellow River wetland reserve in Henan Province, and they have learned to stay away from crowds, with some flying away within 200 metres. Unfortunately, China's wildlife protection list was published in 1988, with the exception of 2003 from the second-class protection of musk deer to the first class, has been more than 30 years, almost no update. Yellow-breasted Bunting is still not listed as a class I or Class II protected animal, but only classified as a "triple animal" (the state's protected terrestrial wildlife of ecological, scientific and social importance) , on a par with sparrows. One of these years, Yellow-breasted Bunting could be eaten out of existence. After the outbreak, the country began to crack down on illegal wildlife hunting and trading, it is also painful.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Endangered yellow-breasted bunting (sparrows) seen occasionally in the Yellow River Wetlands of Henan Province during the National Day holiday in 2019. In the last 40 years, the population has shrunk by 90% 

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Heading towards Taihang Mountains. No cars in front, no people behind.

The highway passes through the Taihang Mountain area, the mountain peak is continuous, in the field of vision half a day does not see a colleague vehicle, the feeling is uncanny. The broadcast reported that various places refueled for Wuhan, donated epidemic prevention materials to Hubei, the air force used military aircraft to deliver emergency supplies, and some foreign donations poured in. Recall watching Wechat last night: Japan's Hanyu Shuiping Kaoshi donated 20,000 masks and a batch of infrared thermometers to Hubei Universities. On the label of the donation box, it reads in eight Chinese characters: Mountains, rivers, exotic lands, Same Moon, same day.

These eight characters are well known. More than 1,200 years ago, they were embroidered on a thousand robes, which were given to Tang Dynasty monks by Japan's Nagaya Emperor. The account of Jianzhen's deeds in the great monk's eastern expedition records that Master Jianzhen was moved by this Gatha and decided to travel to the east to spread the Dharma. A few days ago, Japan evacuated overseas Chinese from Wuhan, more than 100 people on the same plane, found three new cases of coronavirus pneumonia confirmed. Before the plague, China and Japan were united in friendship and faced a test together.

Quick Access to Beijing

Speed along the beijing-kunming highway all the way, nearly 6 o'clock, into the Beijing municipal boundary, into the Beijing security station to slow down the vehicle. The twilight grew dark and the lights yellowed. Wearing protective clothing of the inspectors, hand-held thermometers to measure the temperature of the passengers, no other checks, less than 17 minutes, through the Beijing checkpoint.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Entering the Beijing boundary, all the people on the bus were tested for body temperature

Into Beijing faster than expected. In the radio, the familiar Beijing accent lets me feel at ease. Not a winter can not pass, 17 years ago I also experienced SARS, perhaps the virus in the summer heat will die out. A high school classmate in the group "paranoid" analysis that if the virus killed the human host, they can not survive, the new crown toxicity should be weakened, infectious, and may later become common influenza virus. I think that's a good point, but time is the only criterion.

I didn't expect there would be a second inspection post after entering Beijing. All the vehicles into the capital was led into the Hancun River Service area, the inspectors took over the identity card one by one, machine scanning, a few seconds over a car. This kind of efficiency, than some checkpoint cell phone registration much more convenient.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The inspector scanned his identity card with a machine.

More than 7:00 pm, driving into the capital, the night is fading, traffic flow. Looking back two days, from the small town in Sichuan, to the bustling capital, through three thousand Li, all the way. My Land, my people, everyone loves their country. Love Her, keep her healthy; love her, keep her people safe.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The notice of return to Beijing was pasted on the door of my home

Go home to the community, do not know what kind of inspection. A few days ago, friends on Wechat used to tell tales of being locked out of their communities as tenants returning to Beijing had to go out for 14 days to submit a health certificate from a hospital. The latest news came on February 1st, when the Deputy Secretary General of the government of Beijing made it clear that no community (village) or property department, except those returning from Hubei, had the right to prevent those returning from Beijing with normal temperature tests from entering the community.

Live in Changping overpass near the car near the Community Gate, really quarantine inspection post, two personnel standing in front of a table, check the pedestrians in and out of the community, the community gate vehicle entrance automatic license plate recognition.

On the door of the home is a piece of paper, is the Neighborhood Committee to forward a letter from the Beijing Center for Disease Control and Prevention, asked to return to Beijing residents to inform the neighborhood committee, leave contact information, and self-observation for two weeks. I immediately called the Neighborhood Committee, the other side registered my license plate and contact information. And reported to the unit to the Beijing situation, began home isolation. It's after 8:00 at night and I'm hungry. With their own home dishes fried two dishes, a garlic preserved pork, a stir-fried cabbage.

Good night, Beijing. The Sun will rise again tomorrow. As long as you wait.
